          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1614619678798-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once browned, transfer the mince to a bowl using a slotted spoon (leave as much oil behind as possible!) and add the <strong>smoked paprika</strong>, <strong>ground cumin</strong>, <strong>cayenne pepper</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>– this is your <strong>smoky lean beef mixture</strong></p><p>Cut the <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into chips</p><p>Add the <strong>chips </strong>to a baking tray with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and<strong> pepper</strong>, give everything a good mix up and put the tray in the oven for 20-25 min or until golden and crisp</p>",
